## Commit

Single commit. Conventional Commits:

```text
fix(ci): make cargo publish tiers idempotent for axis-W-only patches

The 0.6.1 BUMP slice bumped axis-W to 0.6.1 while holding axis-E
(fathomdb-embedder-api) at 0.6.0 per Wake d-001. release.yml T1
(publish-rust-t1-embedder-api) ran `cargo publish` unconditionally,
which would have failed with "version already exists" because
crates.io already serves fathomdb-embedder-api@0.6.0 from the 0.6.0
GA train.

Fix: every publish tier (T1-T7) now checks crates.io for the
target crate version before publishing; if the registry already
serves that version, the tier logs "already published; skipping"
and exits 0. Otherwise it publishes normally.

Generalizes for future axis-W-only patches and for partial-
republish retries (if a later RC2 follows an RC1 that partially
published, the already-published tiers no-op cleanly).

Helper script: scripts/release/cargo-publish-if-new.sh (or
chosen shape). TDD coverage in scripts/tests/test_<helper>.sh.

Unblocks 0.6.1-RC1.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
```

