Rust ref defers to docs.rs post-publish + GitHub source link pre-GA per spec.\",\n  \"mkdocs_strict_result\": \"pass (clean — no warnings; build time 0.24s)\",\n  \"quickstart_smoke_equivalence\": \"matches — quickstart's full Python program (docs/getting-started/quickstart.md § Full Python program) is byte-for-byte the body of scripts/release/smoke/smoke-pypi-wheel.sh with print(engine.counters()) added between search() and close(). Same 5 operations in same order: Engine.open → write([]) → search(query) → close() → print('ok'). No divergence; AC-056 gate text and client experience aligned.\",\n  \"deferral_disclosures_visible_from\": [\n    \"compatibility/index.md (performance gates AC-012/013/019/020; no-0.5.x-shim; open-report deferral; logical-id deferral)\",\n    \"reference/errors.md (recovery hint codes + corruption recovery worked example)\",\n    \"reference/python-api.md (open-report 0.6.0 caveat on Engine.open)\",\n    \"reference/typescript-api.md (open-report 0.6.0 caveat + TS-not-yet-parity caveat)\",\n    \"reference/cli.md (logical-id verb deferral + client workaround via --excise-source)\",\n    \"install/typescript.md (TS-not-yet-parity caveat)\",\n    \"getting-started/quickstart.md (open-report deferral inline in step 2)\",\n    \"getting-started/index.md (consolidated 'Deferred for 0.6.0' section)\",\n    \"concepts/index.md (logical-id deferral mentioned in recovery surface section)\",\n    \"release-notes/0.6.0.md (canonical disclosures — unchanged)\"\n  ],\n  \"total_markdown_loc_added\": 1217,\n  \"loc_breakdown\": {\n    \"new_files\": {\n      \"docs/getting-started/quickstart.md\": 173,\n      \"docs/install/python.md\": 81,\n      \"docs/install/typescript.md\": 73,\n      \"docs/install/rust.md\": 78,\n      \"docs/reference/python-api.md\": 167,\n      \"docs/reference/typescript-api.md\": 173,\n      \"docs/reference/cli.md\": 95,\n      \"docs/reference/errors.md\": 102,\n      \"docs/reference/config.md\": 81\n    },\n    \"modified_net\": {\n      \"docs/index.md\": \"+26 (22 → 48)\",\n      \"docs/getting-started/index.md\": \"-53 (103 → 50)\",\n      \"docs/reference/index.md\": \"+25 (8 → 33)\",\n      \"docs/compatibility/index.md\": \"+87 (4 → 91)\",\n      \"docs/concepts/index.md\": \"+97 (5 → 102)\",\n      \"mkdocs.yml\": \"+11 (24 → 35)\"\n    },\n    \"git_diffstat\": \"15 files changed, 1363 insertions(+), 146 deletions(-)\"\n  },\n  \"loc_budget_note\": \"Spec budget was ~500-800 LoC of markdown. Actual additions land at ~1217 net new lines. Overshoot driven by 5 reference pages (python-api 167 + typescript-api 173 + cli 95 + errors 102 + config 81 = 618 LoC) which carry the locked-surface field-by-field documentation that clients need to actually use the SDKs. Each reference page is bounded (≤173 LoC) and cites the authoritative spec rather than duplicating it. Net-negative-LoC bias was applied to guides/operations (left as post-GA stubs) and to concepts/compatibility (60-100 LoC tight overview, not deep treatment). If orchestrator/reviewer wants the LoC under 800, candidates to trim are the worked-example block in errors.md and the per-step prose in quickstart.md, but neither is recommended — both serve concrete client utility.\",\n  \"blockers_encountered\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"agent-verify-strace\",\n      \"description\": \"scripts/agent-verify.sh hits AC-036/AC-037 strace BLOCKER on bare host (no sudo available to install strace). Documented in spec § 'Known flakes' — bootstrap installs strace; this is the 12-S baseline behavior on hosts without strace pre-installed. UNRELATED to docs slice content.\",\n      \"impact\": \"agent-verify reports '0 violation(s), 2 blocker(s)'. lint/typecheck/test/FTS5-injection/ast-scan-{rust,python,ts}/removal-detect all PASS.\",\n      \"resolution\": \"documented; orchestrator/reviewer to confirm strace blocker is acceptable for a docs-only slice. No code or docs change required.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"blockers_NOT_encountered\": [\n    \"mkdocstrings vs basic-theme compat — not exercised (went hand-written per spec rationale).\",\n    \"Python source docstring sparseness — confirmed sparse but moot once hand-written path chosen.\",\n    \"quickstart-vs-smoke divergence — verified equivalent; documented in quickstart_smoke_equivalence above.\",\n    \"pre-GA install paths breaking on dev host — not verified live (docs-only slice; install pages cite the documented commands).\"\n  ],\n  \"agent_verify_result\": \"lint/typecheck/test/FTS5-injection/ast-scan(rust,python,ts)/removal-detect PASS; AC-036/AC-037 strace BLOCKER (host-config, 12-S baseline, no sudo for apt install strace). Tail: 'agent-security: 0 violation(s), 2 blocker(s)'.\",\n  \"next_step_for_orchestrator\": \"promote to 0.6.0-rewrite; respawn codex reviewer for verdict\"\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":132,"cache_read_input_tokens":109865,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":132},"output_tokens":43,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"dc101064-57fc-40f7-b4ef-133cbb382d3a"}
