dev/plans/runs/C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-20260504T022727Z.log:395:{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CQ1egWtHpj6qDnYBGTCYzT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. So the current state:\n1. B.1 was REVERTED - `init_sqlite_runtime` and `multithread_wiring.rs` tests no longer exist in the codebase\n2. Current `THREADSAFE=1` in compile_options\n3. No existing `sqlite3_threadsafe == 2` test (B.1 was reverted, so that test is gone)\n\nThe prompt says \"B.1's `sqlite3_threadsafe == 2` test must still pass (now via build flag rather than runtime config).\" This refers to a test that B.1 added but was reverted - so I need to RECREATE a test first (TDD - failing test first), then implement the build flag.\n\n\nNow I need to check how libsqlite3-sys handles the LIBSQLITE3_FLAGS environment variable in its build script to understand how to wire up the THREADSAFE flag.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3849,"cache_read_input_tokens":40427,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3849},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8996a1e6-f0cf-41f6-bd76-ad56a5a9b42e","uuid":"f29c7759-d09f-4fce-a06b-bbe7cba9e4d2"}
