## Verdict: CONCERN

### 1. [medium] Malformed registry responses are treated as “version absent” and can fall through to publish
Refs: [cargo-publish-if-new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/release/cargo-publish-if-new.sh:120), [cargo-publish-if-new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/release/cargo-publish-if-new.sh:128), [cargo-publish-if-new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/release/cargo-publish-if-new.sh:135), [cargo-publish-if-new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/release/cargo-publish-if-new.sh:160)

The helper comment says non-JSON bodies should return `2`, but the implementation only returns `2` when `curl` itself fails. If crates.io returns HTTP 200 with malformed/truncated JSON, the `jq` check just falls through as false and the helper returns `1`, which drives the “not on registry; publishing” path. Network and 5xx failures are fail-closed, but JSON-shape failures are currently fail-open.

### 2. [low] The tests do not exercise the manifest reader, and the committed fixtures are overwritten at runtime
Refs: [cargo-publish-if-new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/release/cargo-publish-if-new.sh:97), [Cargo.toml](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/Cargo.toml:15), [fathomdb-embedder-api Cargo.toml](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder-api/Cargo.toml:7), [test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/tests/test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh:78), [test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/tests/test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh:124), [test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/tests/test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh:138), [test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/tests/test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh:153), [test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/tests/test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh:167)

Manual inspection says the reader should handle the current inline `version = "0.6.0"` crate and the workspace-inherited crates, but the test suite bypasses that logic in every decision-case by injecting `CARGO_PUBLISH_IF_NEW_LOCAL_VERSION`. The tracked JSON fixtures are also recreated in the test before use, so the committed fixture files are not actually the protected source of truth. This leaves the inline/workspace reader path and fixture wiring less covered than the output JSON suggests.

## What passed on inspection

The helper-script abstraction is the right shape here: one reusable decision point, clear dry-run behavior, and no duplication across seven jobs. The workflow wiring is complete: all T1-T7 publish jobs now call the helper, the original T1→T7 order is preserved, and the existing `if: ${{ inputs.dry_run != true }}` sleep gate is still intact in every tier in [release.yml](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/.github/workflows/release.yml:214).

Pre-release matching is correct in principle because the helper checks exact membership in `versions[].num`, not just max stable version, and the fixtures include an `0.6.1-rc.1` case in [fathomdb-engine.json](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/dev/release/fixtures/cargo-publish-if-new/fathomdb-engine.json:4). Treating yanked versions as already published is also the right publish/no-publish choice. The change set stayed within workflow/script/test areas only; no engine code or manifest versions were edited.

Offline isolation is mostly sound: the test points the helper at a local `python3 -m http.server`, shims `cargo` on `PATH`, and never needs a live crates.io call for the exercised cases in [test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-WF-FIX-1-axis-e-idempotent-publish-20260525T010638Z/scripts/tests/test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh:35).

